                    <font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="3"><br>
                      <b>BiodivERsA Pan-European call for international
                        research proposals on biodiversity and ecosystem
                        services<br>
                      </b>1st November 2010 &#8211; 17th February 2011<br>
                      <br>
                      The BiodivERsA &#8220;Pan-European call for
                      international research proposals on biodiversity
                      and ecosystem services&#8221; has been published on the
                      project website: <a class="moz-txt-link-freetext" href="http://www.eurobiodiversa.org">http://www.eurobiodiversa.org</a><br>
                      <br>
                      Altogether, 9 countries have confirmed their
                      participation in this transnational programme:
                      France, Sweden, Austria, Germany, Spain, Estonia,
                      the Netherlands, Lithuania, and Belgium (formal
                      agreement still expected for Belgium). The total
                      provisional amount of the call is more than 11,1
                      M&#8364;.<br>
                      <br>
                      Scientific teams from these 9 countries will be
                      invited to form transnational research consortia
                      with a total of at least 3 different countries
                      participating in the call, and to submit proposals
                      before the 17th of February 2011. Nevertheless, a
                      mandatory pre-registration of the projects (title,
                      summary and consortium) will have to be done
                      before the 5th of January 2011.<br>
                      <br>
                      The call will address the two following themes,
                      across all ecosystems and organisms:<br>
                      a) Relationships between biodiversity and
                      ecosystem services;<br>
                      b) Valuation of biodiversity and ecosystem
                      services (monetary and non monetary), and better
                      incorporation of biodiversity and ecosystem
                      services into society and policy.<br>
                      <br>
                      The research proposals will be evaluated against
                      criteria of scientific excellence and policy
                      relevance. It is also expected that the European
                      scope of the projects will provide a clearly
                      identified added value to the research carried
                      out.<br>
                      <br>
                      The budget available by agency/country is now
                      online, as well as a FAQ, a partner search tool
                      and the applicant form for indicative purposes
                      only, as an EPSS will be available for the
                      application submission at a later stage). As
                      national eligibility rules are applied in this
                      pan-European call, the potential applicants should
                      contact their National Contact Point for more
                      information (list available on the website).<br>
                      <br>
                      &gt;&gt;&gt; BiodivERsA is a network composed of
                      national organisations funding or managing
                      research programmes on biodiversity across Europe.
                      The objectives of this ERA-Net are to promote the
                      cooperation between funding agencies in the field
                      of biodiversity research and to coordinate
                      research programmes at strategic and management
                      levels to eventually develop and implement joint
                      activities.<br>
                      See: <a href="http://www.eurobiodiversa.org/">http://www.eurobiodiversa.org</a><br>
                    </font><br>
